A '''bank out wagon''' is a [[vehicle]], either towed or self-propelled, with a [[Chute (gravity)|hopper]], used to transport [[grain]] from a [[combine harvester]] to nearby [[Trailer (vehicle)|trailers]] or [[Silo|storage]].<ref>Douglas Beames, Farmers Rice Cooperative Board Member</ref>

