{{Infobox person | name = Emma Mulqueeny | birth_name = Emma Elizabeth Mulqueeny | image = Wikimania sessions 2014 12.JPG | alt = | caption = Mulqueeny speaking at [[Wikimania 2014]] at the [[Barbican Centre]], London | residence = [[Guildford]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1971|7|12}}<ref name="whoswho"/> | birth_place = [[Sidcup]], [[Kent]], [[England]] | nationality = [[British people|British]] | other_names = hubmum | known_for = {{Plainlist| * [[Young Rewired State]] * [[Year Eight|Year 8]] is too Late<ref>[http://mulqueeny.wordpress.com/2011/08/10/year-8-is-too-late/ Year 8 is too late] mulqueeny.wordpress.com 2011-08-10</ref>}} | website = {{URL|https://mulqueeny.wordpress.com}} }}
'''Emma Elizabeth Mulqueeny''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|OBE}} ([[Given name|née]] '''Knight;''' born 12 July 1971) is the co-founder and [[chief executive officer]] of [[Young Rewired State]] and [[Rewired State]].<ref name="founders">{{Cite web |title = National Hack The Government Day |work = Rewired State |accessdate = 2009-01-21 |date = 2009 |url = http://rewiredstate.org |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090121063517/http://rewiredstate.org |archivedate = 2009-01-21 |df = }}</ref><ref name="whoswho">{{Who's Who | surname = MULQUEENY | othernames = Emma Elizabeth | id = U258294 | volume = 2014 | edition = online edition via [[Oxford University Press]]}} {{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Blog Entries by Emma Mulqueeny | work = [[Huffington Post]] | accessdate = 2014-08-19 | date = 2012-01-10 | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/emma-mulqueeny }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Emma Mulqueeny | work = Nesta | accessdate = 2014-08-19 | url = http://www.nesta.org.uk/10-tech-heroes-good/emma-mulqueeny }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Emma Mulqueeny columns | work = The Guardian | accessdate = 2014-08-19 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/profile/emma-mulqueeny }}</ref><ref name=rewired>{{Cite web |title = The Team |work = Rewired State |accessdate = 2014-08-19 |date = 2014 |url = http://rewiredstate.org/team |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140816151053/http://rewiredstate.org/team |archivedate = 2014-08-16 |df = }}</ref> She is a Commissioner for the Speaker's Commission on [[E-democracy|Digital Democracy]] and a [[Google]] [[Fellow]].<ref>[http://new.livestream.com/wikimania/saturday2014 Emma Mulqueeny, Young Rewired State at Wikimania 2014] in London</ref><ref name=ict>{{YouTube|title=Computer Science, Math, and ICT—Where Does Programming Fit?: Emma Mulqueeny|id=nuLhNPwjeE8}}</ref><ref name=yrstube>{{YouTube|id=cjVDE8PW0-s|title=Emma Mulqueeny - Founder of Young Rewired State - The YRS story #yrs2013}}</ref>
She is the daughter of Kenneth G Knight and Sara Nicholls ([[Given name|née]] McArtney), and was educated at the [[University of Surrey]].
==Awards and honours== Mulqueeny was included in the 166th annual edition of ''[[Who’s Who]]'', and was voted onto the [[Wired (magazine)|Wired]] 100 list, [[East London Tech City|Tech City]] 100 and [[British Interactive Media Association|BIMA]] Hot 10. She was voted one of the top ten women in technology by ''[[The Guardian]]'' and was named in the top ten Tech Heroes for Good by [[Nesta (charity)|NESTA]].<ref name=rewired/><ref>[http://www.parliament.uk/business/commons/the-speaker/speakers-commission-on-digital-democracy/members/emma-mulqueeny/ Emma is the founder of Rewired State and Young Rewired State: Coding a better country.]</ref>
She was appointed as an [[Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] (OBE) in the 2016 Birthday Honours for services to technology and education.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61608|supp=y|page=B13|date=11 June 2016}}</ref>
