'''Hydroacoustic Position Reference''' is a system to measure the relative position between a transmitter and a receiver under water. It is sometimes used for vessels with [[dynamic positioning]] to either measure the relative position between a fixed underwater transmitter or to a mobile under water vehicle (for example [[Remotely operated underwater vehicle|ROV]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Kongsberg: Acoustic underwater positioning and navigation systems HiPAP and HPR|url=http://www.km.kongsberg.com/ks/web/nokbg0240.nsf/AllWeb/FF57C18363FAD917C1256A7E002B9F2F?OpenDocument}}</ref>

