{{advert|date=October 2015}} {{COI|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox company | name = Krossblade Aerospace Systems | type = Private | logo = [[File:Logo Krossblade Aerospace.png|frameless|Krossblade Aerospace Systems]] | foundation = 2014 | founder = Daniel Lubrich and Austin Kipp | location = [[United States]] [[Singapore]] | area_served = Global locations | industry = [[Aerospace]]/[[Aviation]] | products = SkyCruiser, SkyProwler | owner = | homepage = {{URL|http://www.krossblade.com}} }}
'''Krossblade Aerospace Systems''' is an aviation company founded in 2014 in [[Phoenix, Arizona]], USA. The company is known for developing a 5-seat hybrid, vertical take-off and landing, [[VTOL]] concept, SkyCruiser, and for its [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|drone]]/[[Unmanned aerial vehicle|UAV]] prototype, SkyProwler.<ref name= "PopularMechanics">{{cite web|last= Hambling| first= David| url= http://www.popularmechanics.com/technology/aviation/news/watch-the-skycruiser-flying-car-transform-from-helicopter-to-plane-in-mid-air-17374210|title=Watch the SkyCruiser Flying Car Transform From Helicopter to Plane in Mid-Air |publisher=Popular Mechanics|date= 2014-10-31| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref name= "Gizmag">{{cite web|last= Szondy| first= David|url= http://www.gizmag.com/krossblade-skycruiser-flying-car/34392/ |title= Krossblade's SkyCruiser merges airplane, quadcopter and car |publisher=Gizmag |date= 2014-10-25| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last= Shadbolt| first= Peter|url= http://edition.cnn.com/2014/11/14/tech/innovation/tomorrow-transformed-race-to-build-flying-car/ |title= The race is on for flying car start ups |publisher=[[CNN]] |date= 2014-11-14| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.reuters.com/video/2014/10/27/an-airplane-helicopter-and-car-all-in-on?videoId=346716869 |title= An airplane, helicopter and car, all in one |publisher= [[Reuters]] |date= 2014-10-27| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last= Scharnhorst| first= Emily |url= https://news.yahoo.com/blogs/oddnews/here-s-an-airplane--helicopter--and-car-%E2%80%94-all-in-one-182041739.html|title= Here's an Airplane, Helicopter, and Car — All in One|publisher=[[Yahoo]] News |date= 2014-10-28| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= Satya Swaroop Dash| url= http://www.crazyengineers.com/threads/skycruiser-airplane-skyprowler-drone-feature-vertical-take-off-landing.77116/ |title= SkyCruiser Airplane & SkyProwler Drone Feature Vertical Take-off & Landing |publisher= Crazy Engineers |date= 2014-10-27| accessdate=2015-01-26}}</ref> Both aircraft employ the switchblade transformation mechanism to transform from a [[multirotor]] [[aircraft]] for vertical take-off and landing, to a pure [[wing]]ed aircraft, for rapid and efficient cruise.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/posttv/business/technology/aircraft-combines-a-helicopter-airplane-and-car/2014/10/27/262afe68-5e13-11e4-827b-2d813561bdfd_video.html |title= Aircraft combines a helicopter, airplane and car |publisher= [[Washington Post]] |date= 2014-10-27| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/388089/scitech/technology/watch-this-hybrid-car-is-part-plane-part-helicopter-too|title= This hybrid car is part plane, part helicopter too |publisher= GMA News Online |date= 2014-11-14| accessdate=2015-01-26}}</ref>
==Krossblade SkyCruiser== SkyCruiser is a concept of a vertical take-off and landing transformer aircraft with limited road drive capability. It has 5 seats and is powered by a [[Hybrid vehicle|hybrid]] power train.<ref>{{cite web|author= Vikas Shukla| url= http://www.valuewalk.com/2014/10/krossblades-skycruiser-airplane/|title= Krossblade’s SkyCruiser Is An Airplane That Turns Into Car Upon Landing|publisher= Value Walk| date= 2014-10-29| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= Ben Griffin| url= http://recombu.com/cars/article/krossblade-skycruiser-is-a-flying-car-like-no-other|title= Krossblade SkyCruiser is a flying car like no other|publisher= Recombu| date= 2014-10-30| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref> While all rotors and propellers are driven by electric motors, the electric energy is produced by a 400&nbsp;hp internal combustion engine mated to a generator.<ref name= "Gizmag"/> A small battery provides backup storage of electric energy enabling SkyCruiser to briefly fly purely on stored electric power. SkyCruiser is able to fly at speeds in excess of 300&nbsp;mph with a range of around 1,000 miles.<ref name= "Gizmag"/> Although capable of driving on roads, SkyCruiser is optimized for flight. Fast cruise bridges larger distances rapidly, while the VTOL capability enables it to land at or very close to its passengers’ destination.<ref>{{cite web|last= Prigg| first= Mark| url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-2812978/The-ultimate-fly-drive-package-SkyCruiser-merges-aeroplane-quadcopter-car.html |title= The ultimate fly drive package: SkyCruiser merges an aeroplane, quadcopter and a car |publisher= [[Daily Mail]] |date= 2014-10-29| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last= Brindusescu|first= Gabriel | url= http://www.autoevolution.com/news/krossblade-skycruiser-is-part-hybrid-helicopter-part-personal-jet-video-88369.html|title= Krossblade SkyCruiser Is Part Hybrid Helicopter, Part Personal Jet |publisher= Autoevolution |date= 2014-10-31| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last= Hopton|first= Eric| url= http://www.redorbit.com/news/technology/1113270772/flying-car-prototypes-krossblade-aerospace-systems-110214/ |title= SkyCruiser Flying Car Aims To Slash Travel Times|publisher= Red Orbit| date= 2014-11-02| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref> SkyCruiser is scheduled to come to market at the end of the current decade.<ref name= "FlightGlobal">{{cite web|url= http://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/video-39transformer39-uav-touted-to-parcel-delivery-406094/|title= 'Transformer' UAV touted to parcel delivery market|publisher= Flight Global| date= 2014-11-14| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref>
==Krossblade SkyProwler== [[File:Krossblade SkyProwler Hover VTOL 800.jpg|200px|right|title=Krossblade SkyProwler]] SkyProwler is a UAV/drone prototype used by Krossblade to develop the essential mechanisms and concepts for the larger SkyCruiser.<ref name= "PopularMechanics"/><ref name= "Gizmag"/> It is a purely electrical aircraft that utilizes the switchblade mechanism to transform from multirotor-mode for VTOL to a pure aircraft mode for fast and efficient cruise. Possible applications include delivery.<ref name= "FlightGlobal"/> SkyProwler flies with speeds of up to 55&nbsp;mph.<ref>{{cite web|last= Ramachandran| first= Sanjeev|url= http://www.devicemag.com/2014/10/29/skycruiser-hybrid-vehicle-can-fly-like-a-copter-and-cruise-along-highways-like-a-car/ |title= SkyCruiser Hybrid Vehicle Can Fly Like a Copter and Cruise Along Highways Like a Car |publisher= Device Magazine| date= 2014-10-29| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref>
==Switchblade mechanism== Rather than employing a rigid frame to mount motors and rotors as is done in quadcopters and other multirotors, in the switchblade mechanism motors and rotors are mounted on movable arms. These arms can pivot and so enable storage of the rotors and motors inside the fuselage, where they do not cause aerodynamic drag and hence enable to aircraft to fly faster and more efficient. Compared to a pure winged aircraft, the VTOL system, including the switchblade mechanism, increases the weight of an aircraft by around 15%.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.europeanpilot.com/krossblade-skycruiser-joins-race-flying-car/|title= Krossblade SkyCruiser joins race for a flying car|publisher= European Pilot| accessdate=2015-01-24}}</ref>
