'''Salux cloth''' also called '''Salux nylon''', is a type of [[Japan]]ese [[washcloth]] originating in 1966 made of part [[nylon]] and [[polyester]].<ref name="salu_Orig">{{Cite web| title = A shower is not a shower without a Salux| work = Salux Shop| accessdate = 2015-07-05| url = http://www.saluxshop.com/}}</ref><ref name="nyti_AtMa">{{Cite web| title = At Makeup Alley, Advice From Online Peers| last = Louis | first = Catherine Saint| work = New York Times| date = 27 July 2011| accessdate = 2015-07-05| url = https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/28/fashion/at-makeup-alley-advice-from-online-peers.html}}</ref> The cloth is known for its ability to soften and smooth skin. Salux may also reduced [[ingrown hair]]s after shaving and help [[Exfoliation (cosmetology)|exfoliation]].<ref name="thew_Howt">{{Cite web| title = How to take a perfect shower| author = Leslie Turnbull| work = The Week| date = 2015-05-19| accessdate = 2015-07-05| url = http://theweek.com/articles/555409/how-take-perfect-shower}}</ref> Hannah Johnson of xoVain describes the cloth as a "total game-changer".<ref name="xova_OMG!">{{Cite web| title = OMG! This Japanese Washcloth Is A Total Game-Changer| author = Hannah Johnson| work = xoVain| date = 2013-08-29| accessdate = 2015-07-05| url = http://www.xovain.com/skin/best-washcloth-ever}}</ref> Salux won the Japanese Invention Award in 1974.<ref name="baby_baby">{{Cite web| title = babyassface: And the winner of the Japanese invention prize is... a washcloth?| work = BabyAssFace| date = 2008-09-02| accessdate = 2015-07-05| url = http://www.babyassface.com/babyassface/2008/09/and-the-winner-of-the-japanese-invention-prize-is-a-washcloth.html}}</ref>
